{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.104",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 104,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 104 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:1",
      "text": "Give glory to the Lord, and call upon his name: declare his deeds among the Gentiles.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:2",
      "text": "Sing to him, yea sing praises to him: relate all his wondrous works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:3",
      "text": "Glory ye in his holy name: let the heart of them rejoice that seek the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:4",
      "text": "Seek ye the Lord, and be strengthened: seek his face evermore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:5",
      "text": "Remember his marvellous works which he hath done; his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:6",
      "text": "O ye seed of Abraham his servant; ye sons of Jacob his chosen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:7",
      "text": "He is the Lord our God: his judgments are in all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:8",
      "text": "He hath remembered his covenant for ever: the word which he commanded to a thousand generations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:9",
      "text": "Which he made to Abraham; and his oath to Isaac:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:10",
      "text": "And he appointed the same to Jacob for a law, and to Israel for an everlasting testament:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:11",
      "text": "Saying: To thee will I give the land of Chanaan, the lot of your inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:12",
      "text": "When they were but a small number: yea very few, and sojourners therein:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:13",
      "text": "And they passed from nation to nation, and from one kingdom to another people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:14",
      "text": "He suffered no man to hurt them: and he reproved kings for their sakes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:15",
      "text": "Touch ye not my anointed: and do no evil to my prophets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:16",
      "text": "And he called a famine upon the land: and he broke in pieces all the support of bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:17",
      "text": "He sent a man before them: Joseph, who was sold for a slave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:18",
      "text": "They humbled his feet in fetters: the iron pierced his soul,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:19",
      "text": "Until his word came. The word of the Lord inflamed him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:20",
      "text": "The king sent, and he released him: the ruler of the people, and he set him at liberty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:21",
      "text": "He made him master of his house, and ruler of all his possession.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:22",
      "text": "That he might instruct his princes as himself, and teach his ancients wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:23",
      "text": "And Israel went into Egypt: and Jacob was a sojourner in the land of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:24",
      "text": "And he increased his people exceedingly: and strengthened them over their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:25",
      "text": "He turned their heart to hate his people: and to deal deceitfully with his servants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:26",
      "text": "He sent Moses his servant: Aaron the man whom he had chosen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:27",
      "text": "He gave them power to shew them signs, and his wonders in the land of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:28",
      "text": "He sent darkness, and made it obscure: and grieved not his words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:29",
      "text": "He turned their waters into blood, and destroyed their fish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:30",
      "text": "Their land brought forth frogs, in the inner chambers of their kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:31",
      "text": "He spoke, and there came divers sorts of flies and sciniphs in all their coasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:32",
      "text": "He gave them hail for rain, a burning fire in the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:33",
      "text": "And he destroyed their vineyards and their fig trees: and he broke in pieces the trees of their coasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:34",
      "text": "He spoke, and the locust came, and the bruchus, of which there was no number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:35",
      "text": "And they devoured all the grass in their land, and consumed all the fruit of their ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:36",
      "text": "And he slew all the firstborn in their land: the firstfruits of all their labour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:37",
      "text": "And he brought them out with silver and gold: and there was not among their tribes one that was feeble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:38",
      "text": "Egypt was glad when they departed: for the fear of them lay upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:39",
      "text": "He spread a cloud for their protection, and fire to give them light in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:40",
      "text": "They asked, and the quail came: and he filled them with the bread of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:41",
      "text": "He opened the rock, and waters flowed: rivers ran down in the dry land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:42",
      "text": "Because he remembered his holy word, which he had spoken to his servant Abraham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.43",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:43",
      "text": "And he brought forth his people with joy, and his chosen with gladness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.44",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:44",
      "text": "And he gave them the lands of the Gentiles: and they possessed the labours of the people:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.104.45",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 104,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 104:45",
      "text": "That they might observe his justifications, and seek after his law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
